      <biogHist id="md5-dffce1852571e73712e66946472ef62f">
        <p>Author, Poet, 1901-  .  Son of Arthur and Gertrude Balmer Watt, Ted Watt was a bush pilot, reporter, and author.  As a reporter he flew on the first airmail flight to Aklavik in 1928, and he covered the shooting of the Mad Trapper, Albert Johnson.  He was a naval intelligence officer in World War II, earning the rank of Lieutenant Commander.  Mr. Watt was a member of the information branch of Health and Welfare in Ottawa from 1957 to 1969.  He is the author of numerous magazine articles, poems, and books, including a history of the Edmonton Grads and Great Bear, which describes the Great Bear Lake region.</p>
      </biogHist>
